                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_fast" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><form type="lemma"><orth>fast</orth></form><usg><lang/></usg><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>совет</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>advice</q></abv:tr></sense><re><form type="lemma"><orth>fasti xaʒi</orth></form><sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>мудрый</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>wise</q></abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>советчик</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>advisor</q></abv:tr></sense><sense><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">буквально</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">literally</note><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>хаджи совета</q></abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">буквально</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">literally</note><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>hadji of an advice</q></abv:tr></sense></sense></re><abv:exampleGrp><abv:example><quote>dæ fidæ Acæ mæ fastbæl færsidæ</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>твой отец Аца спросил бы у меня совета</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>your father Atsa would ask me for advice</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 70</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example><quote>fasti arǧæwttæ</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>нравоучительные сказки</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>moralistic tales</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 91, 185</biblScope></bibl></abv:example></abv:exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Из %ifarst%i, лексикализованное прош. причастие от <ref type="xr" target="#entry_færsyn"/> ‘спрашивать’; точное значение „спрос“. Отсюда <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævast"/> (← %iæ-fast%i) ‘без спроса’, ‘самовольный’, ‘внезапный’, д. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xevast"/> (← %ixe-fast%i) ‘своенравный’. В %ifast%i (из %ifarst%i) выпал %ir%i перед сибилянтом, как в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tas"/> ‘страх’ (из %i*tars%i), <ref type="xr" target="#entry_baz"/> ‘подушка’ (из %i*barz%i), <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xæzgūl"/> ‘любовница’ (из %ixærzgul%i) и др. Ср. выпадение %ir%i в <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>fštw, ʽβštw</w></mentioned>, прош. причастие от <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>pṛs-</w> <gloss><q>спрашивать</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">From %ifarst%i, a lexicalized past participle of <ref type="xr" target="#entry_færsyn"/> ‘ask’; the exact meaning is ‘demand’. The following words are also from it: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævast"/> (← %iæ-fast%i) ‘without asking’, ‘self-willed’, ‘sudden’, Digor <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xevast"/> (← %ixe-fast%i) ‘wilful’. In %ifast%i (from %ifarst%i) the consonant %ir%i fell before the sibilant, as in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tas"/> ‘fear’ (from %i*tars%i), <ref type="xr" target="#entry_baz"/> ‘pillow’ (from %i*barz%i), <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xæzgūl"/> ‘mistress’ (from %ixærzgul%i) etc. Cf. the fall of %ir%i in <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>fštw, ʽβštw</w></mentioned>, a past participle of <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>pṛs-</w> <gloss><q>ask</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>